item.title: Ninja Star Shield (Made From Scratch!)
item.dc:creator: @the_wanderer The Wanderer
item.description:
@the_wanderer wrote:

Ix Soulcist xI:

You are showing us a lot of models under a certain amount of time. I would take the time to work on them more.

I disagree. Since he is just starting out he needs a lot of pointers on these new models he is creating. Then he can take the time to perfect his skills once he gets the basics down.


Just slight nit-picking. You probably triangulated it and it did that on purpose. Pro-tip, don’t triangulate your models before you take pictures of the wireframe. They look nicer without all of those pesky triangles.

Also, work on your color scheme a bit more. Yellow and black down go together that well unless you want to look like a bumblebee. You could also do with some more detail, but you are learning so that’s fine. Keep it up!
